WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.120 --> 00:00:06.700
 This video shows how Windows 8 users can start safe mode. 

00:00:10.980 --> 00:00:13.760
 The Safe Mode is a diagnostic mode that allows you 

00:00:13.769 --> 00:00:15.450
 Can use Windows with basic drivers. 

00:00:16.960 --> 00:00:20.440
 If you have error messages or software problems with Windows 8 

00:00:20.880 --> 00:00:22.900
 then you can restart in Safe Mode by restarting 

00:00:22.910 --> 00:00:26.150
 keep working and solve the problem. 

00:00:26.680 --> 00:00:28.980
 To start safe mode from Windows 

00:00:28.980 --> 00:00:32.220
 press the Windows and the I key simultaneously. 

00:00:33.820 --> 00:00:38.500
 Click Change PC settings to open the PC settings menu. 

00:00:38.510 --> 00:00:42.489
 Select Update and restore from the PC Settings menu. 

00:00:43.220 --> 00:00:46.799
 Now click on Recovery in the Update and Recovery menu. 

00:00:47.380 --> 00:00:50.800
 Under Advanced Startup, click Restart Now. 

00:00:53.020 --> 00:00:56.400
 Select Troubleshooting on the Choose an Option screen. 

00:00:56.960 --> 00:01:01.900
 Click Advanced Options, Startup Settings, and then Restart. 

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:06.060
 Your computer will be restarted. 

00:01:06.070 --> 00:01:08.830
 Another screen appears with Start-up settings. 

00:01:09.800 --> 00:01:15.420
 Select the safe mode option if you want to use the F1 to F9 keys. 

00:01:18.990 --> 00:01:22.320
 Log in to your computer with the name and password of your account. 

00:01:22.800 --> 00:01:26.020
 The computer opens the desktop in Safe Mode. 

00:01:26.660 --> 00:01:29.539
 To close Safe Mode, press simultaneously 

00:01:29.540 --> 00:01:31.820
 the Windows and the I key. 

00:01:33.500 --> 00:01:35.660
 Click On / Off and then Restart 

00:01:35.860 --> 00:01:37.780
 to start your computer normally. 

